CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 25, 1958, pg. A15, reads: "Lincoln Park Auxiliary - Members of the very active Lincoln Park Auxiliary, Penn Township, held a fund-raising tea last Sunday at the center which drew an interested group of citizens. Left to right are Mrs. Essie Watkins, past president and master of ceremonies; Miss Sally Mungin, executive director of the Wilkinsburg YWCA; Richard S. Dowdy, director of industrial relations of the Urban League of Pittsburgh and Mrs. Beatrice Hoar, area director of the Penn Hills - Wilkinsburg YWCA. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of Lincoln Park Auxiliary, Penn Township Essie Watkins, Sally Mungin, Richard S. Dowdy, and Beatrice Hoar posed during fundraising tea
